mating experiment = 6461 x 14229-5 selected on EK (Erythromycin + Kanamycin antibiotics)

Sample A to J are different colonies collected from the same experiment.
Number of samples = 9
Sample D was deleted as it was showing a contamination on Illumina reads.
Fanta files in this folder correspond to Unicycler assemblies using Illumina + Nanopore sequences.

Parental strains = 6461 (assembly number: 462) and 14229-5 (assembly number: 470)
Previous Illumina sequencing of colonies (assembly numbers 466, 476, 492) showed 6461 was the recipient strain.

Aim: Compare the 9 sequences to
- verify that 6461 is always the recipient strain
- compare in detail the whole genome to see if insertions/deletions events are the same
- compare in detail the whole genome to see if insertions/deletions events always happen at the same place in the genome













